<item>
            <title>[SOLR-17367] org.apache.solr.cli.PostTool is ignoring -params option</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-17367</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;org.apache.solr.cli.PostTool is ignoring the -params option.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;According to the documentation here &lt;a href=&quot;https://solr.apache.org/guide/solr/latest/indexing-guide/post-tool.html,&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://solr.apache.org/guide/solr/latest/indexing-guide/post-tool.html,&lt;/a&gt; the -params option is to be used when specifying a different separator (for example the tab separator)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, looking through the code (&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/solr/blob/main/solr/core/src/java/org/apache/solr/cli/PostTool.java#L244&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/solr/blob/main/solr/core/src/java/org/apache/solr/cli/PostTool.java#L244&lt;/a&gt;) it seems that even if the option is mentioned, it is never used afterwards.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;I encountered the issue using docker solr version 9.6.1&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
